  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0dba\u0dd6\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dcf \u0db8\u0dd2\u0da7\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dda \u0db1\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0dd2 \u0db6\u0dbb \u0db1\u0dd0\u0dad\u0dd4\u0dc0 \u0d9c\u0ddc\u0dc0\u0dd3\u0db1\u0dca \u0d85\u0db4\u0dc4\u0dc3\u0dd4\u0dad\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0da7",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Farmers are in trouble without proper weight of urea bale",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "It was reported from the Dambulla Agricultural Service Center today (18th) that the farmers as well as the Agricultural Service Officers are in dire straits due to the lack of proper quantity of urea fertilizer which is brought from India and distributed to the farmers.",
        "The release of a 50 kg bundle of fertilizer by the Ministry of Agriculture to farmers' organizations at a cost of ten thousand rupees was implemented at the Dambulla Agricultural Service Center.",
        "The government had announced to give 40 kg of urea fertilizer to one acre. The farmers started accusing that only 20 kg of urea is given to 1 acre of rice cultivation through the Dambulla Agricultural Service Office.",
        "Dambulla Agricultural Service Divisional Officer Mr. Sampath Kumara said that due to not getting the required amount of fertilizer, only 1500 bundles of fertilizer have been received.",
        "Therefore, since it is not possible to provide 40 kilos per acre, it was decided to give 20 kilos per acre in order to do justice to all.",
        "However, due to the lack of 50 kg of fertilizer in the Dambulla Agricultural Service Office, the leaders of the farmers' organizations were in dire straits, and upon the request of the farmers, the farmers were able to weigh the received fertilizer with a scale inside the warehouse.",
        "Fertilizers were greatly reduced in the packages which were noted to contain 50 kg. There were 48, 47, 49 kilos in some sacks, and at the same time there were 40 kilos instead of 50 kilos in some packages.",
        "However, the representatives of the farmers' organizations said that the officials had to face many serious problems when they were going to take 50 kilos and weigh them and distribute them to the farmers.",
        "The farmers also say that due to the lack of 50 kilos, it is less possible to get money for 20 kilos per person. The farmers' representatives also point out that the incident of fertilizer distribution raises many other issues in the farmers' organizations in the villages."
      ],
